  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: The first character in the topic input can't be cleared. In result, user can't clear the whole topic to type a new one. She needs to leave public chat screen and open it again to start with an empty topic.\r\n\r\nIn the screenshot below, \"j\" can't be cleared. Also, please note a misalignment (iOS only) between \"#\" and topic name: \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/36627710-24cc01fa-1947-11e8-9265-02ab84ff6856.png\" width=\"300\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nWhole topic can be cleared. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nThe first character of the topic can't be cleared.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to Home\r\n- Click \"+\" and join public chat\r\n- Write a chat topic\r\n- Try to clear the topic\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.15, 834ae3\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS\r\n* Tested on iPhone 6 (iOS 11.2.1) and Samsung Galaxy S2 (Android 7)",
